titleStmt.title: The malignants inquest: or, A jury of cavaleirs (at Oxford) impeaching, condemning, and hanging one another. Where Ignatius Holy-water an Arch-bishop, Cathedrall Congee an Arch-deacon, Sir Bounteous Project one of His Majesties Privie Councell, Sir Bancrupt Hadland a Commissioner of Array, and Dammee Mouth-Gnu in the army, chiefe commander, are legally tryed and sentenced accordingly.
